'''蘋果園區'''（{{lang-en|'''Apple Park'''}}），原稱為'''Apple Campus 2'''，位於[[美國|美國]][[加州|加州]][[庫比蒂諾_(加利福尼亞州)|庫帕提諾]]蘋果園區路1號（1 Apple Park Way），土地面積達{{convert|176|acre|ha|abbr=off}}，是[[蘋果公司|蘋果公司]]的[[蘋果公司總部|公司總部]]新址。當時仍在建設中的蘋果園區於2017年4月向員工開放<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.apple.com/tw/newsroom/2017/02/apple-park-opens-to-employees-in-april/ |title=Apple Park 將於四月對員工開放 |access-date=2017-06-13 |archive-date=2021-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514070317/https://www.apple.com/tw/newsroom/2017/02/apple-park-opens-to-employees-in-april/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，取代了於1993年開幕在無限循環1號的原有總部<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2016/05/31/apple-campus-2-drone-flyover/|title=Apple Campus 2 Looking Good in New Drone Flyover|first=Don|last=Reisinger|date=2016-05-31|work=Fortune|access-date=2016-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160710103308/http://fortune.com/2016/05/31/apple-campus-2-drone-flyover/|archive-date=2016-07-10|url-status=live}}</ref>，以解決昔日因舊總部建築不敷使用而需分散各地辦公的問題。

此園區主樓的規模和圓形地面建築設計都是由[[诺曼·福斯特|諾曼·福斯特]]設計<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinteriors.co.uk/new-apple-headquarters-best-office-building-world-designed-london/|title=''New Apple Headquarters The Best Office Building In The World, Designed In London''|access-date=2019-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525084939/http://www.businessinteriors.co.uk/new-apple-headquarters-best-office-building-world-designed-london/|archive-date=2019-05-25|url-status=live}}</ref>，其空中鳥瞰的圓環形狀結構贏得媒體暱稱其為「宇宙飛船」<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.macworld.co.uk/feature/apple/complete-guide-apple-park-apples-new-spaceship-campus-3489704/|title=Complete guide to Apple Park, Apple's new 'spaceship' campus|last=Moore|first=Amy|work=Macworld UK|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170507095013/http://www.macworld.co.uk/feature/apple/complete-guide-apple-park-apples-new-spaceship-campus-3489704/|archive-date=2017-05-07|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2013/11/a-glimpse-into-apples-crazy-new-spaceship-headquarters/|title=Look Inside Apple's Spaceship Headquarters With 24 All-New Renderings|last=VanHemert|first=Kyle|work=WIRED|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321104602/https://www.wired.com/2013/11/a-glimpse-into-apples-crazy-new-spaceship-headquarters|archive-date=2017-03-21|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="VBtree" />。其位於郊區的建築採用[[新未來主義|新未來主義]]風格，大樓總長度為1.46平方公里，在一棟約0.26平方公里的中央四層圓形建築中容納了12,000多名員工。蘋果公司的聯合創始人[[史蒂夫·乔布斯|史蒂夫·乔布斯]]希望園區看起來不像商業園區，而是更像一個自然避難所。園區的80%面積由綠地組成，種植了庫比蒂諾地區的耐旱樹木和本土植物，主樓的中央庭院設有人工[[池塘|池塘]]<ref name="VBtree">{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/06/04/a-look-at-apples-insanely-ambitious-tree-planting-plans-for-its-new-spaceship-campus/|title=A look at Apple's insanely ambitious tree-planting plans for its new spaceship campus|first=Chris|last=O'Brien|date=2016-06-04|work=VentureBeat|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819202441/https://venturebeat.com/2016/06/04/a-look-at-apples-insanely-ambitious-tree-planting-plans-for-its-new-spaceship-campus/|archive-date=2017-08-19|url-status=live}}</ref>。建築物頂端鋪設大量[[太陽能板|太陽能板]]，供電能力為17 MW（[[百萬瓦|百萬瓦]]），使得建築可幾乎以太陽能供電<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://udn.com/news/story/7086/2302050 |title=賈伯斯的最後遺產：新總部「Apple Park」4月開始啟用！ |access-date=2017-02-23 |archive-date=2021-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514070337/https://udn.com/news/story/7086/2302050 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

除了主建築以外，另外還設有兩棟獨立於主建築的研發大樓，以及健身中心和訪客中心等附屬建築。蘋果園區還有一個可容納1,000人的史蒂夫·喬布斯劇院（Steve Jobs Theater），供產品發布會之用，無需如以往要租用其他場地。2019年5月17日，蘋果公司在蘋果園區中庭舉行典禮，宣布園區正式開幕。

== 歷史 ==
2006年4月，蘋果公司時任行政總裁[[史蒂夫·喬布斯|史蒂夫·喬布斯]]向[[庫比蒂諾_(加利福尼亞州)|庫比蒂諾]]市議會宣布，指該公司已收購了9處毗鄰的物業，以建造該公司第二個園區—Apple Campus 2<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cupertino.org/index.aspx?page=26&recordid=696&returnURL=%2findex.aspx |title=News : Apple Campus 2 Project Update |publisher=Cupertino |date= |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archive-date=2013-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130709153522/http://www.cupertino.org/index.aspx?page=26&recordid=696&returnURL=%2Findex.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2006/08/07/live-from-wwdc-2006-steve-jobs-keynote/|title=Live from WWDC 2006: Steve Jobs keynote|website=Engadget|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。蘋果公司透過[[漢斯有限合夥公司|漢斯有限合夥公司]]購買所需的物業<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sanjose.bizjournals.com/sanjose/stories/2006/04/17/daily70.html|title=Apple teams with Texas firm on new Cupertino campus|work=San Jose Business Journal|author=Sharon Simonson|date=2006-04-21|access-date=2010-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061126224847/http://sanjose.bizjournals.com/sanjose/stories/2006/04/17/daily70.html|archive-date=2006-11-26|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Chandler2006>{{cite news|last1=Chandler|first1=Michele|title=How Apple found 50 acres in Cupertino and why they paid big bucks for it|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/mld/mercurynews/14422699.htm|access-date=2014-09-27|work=San Jose Mercury-News|date=2006-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060628080011/http://www.mercurynews.com/mld/mercurynews/14422699.htm|archive-date=2006-06-28}}</ref>，該公司至少在某些情況下沒有透露蘋果公司為最終買家的事實<ref name=Chandler2006 />；當地一家商業房地產經紀公司的合夥人菲利普斯·馬哈尼（Phillips Mahaney）指出，為了防止成本飆升，同時不向競爭對手透露該公司的計劃<ref name=Chandler2006 />，這是試圖安排購買由不同地塊的獨立擁有人組成的連續土地的常見做法。這些房產的賣家包括SummerHill Homes（一塊{{convert|8|acre|ha|disp=or|abbr=off}}的土地），以及[[惠普|惠普]]（在庫比蒂諾園區的三座建築）<ref name=Chandler2006 />。

新總部的構想是由喬布斯與蘋果公司前首席設計師[[乔纳森·艾维|莊拿芬·伊夫]]提出的<ref>{{cite web|last=Tetzeli|first=Rick|title=''Why Jony Ive Is Apple's Design Genius''|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/innovation/jony-ive-apple-design-genius-180967232/|date=December 2017|publisher=Smithsonian|access-date=2018-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180517010027/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/innovation/jony-ive-apple-design-genius-180967232/|archive-date=2018-05-17|url-status=live}}</ref>。伊夫是蘋果公司直接選擇為該項目設計，他跟[[诺曼·福斯特|霍朗明]]密切地合作了五年，二人從玻璃面板到電梯按鈕的設計了每一個細節<ref>{{Cite news|last=Passariello|first=Christina|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-jony-ive-masterminded-apples-new-headquarters-1501063201|title=How Jony Ive Masterminded Apple's New Headquarters|date=2017-07-26|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2020-02-16|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/5014495a-98ce-11e9-8cfb-30c211dcd229|title=Subscribe to read {{!}} Financial Times|website=www.ft.com|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。直到2008年4月，蘋果公司還尚未申請得到施工所需的許可，因此預計該項目在2010年不會如最初提出的那樣準備就緒；然而，現場的建築物由蘋果公司持有以供其運營。2010年11月，《[[聖荷西信使報|聖荷西信使報]]》披露蘋果公司又再購下{{le|惠普公司|HP Inc.}}不再使用位於普魯內里奇大道以北的{{convert|98|acre|ha}}閒置土地<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2010/11/24/apple-makes-big-land-purchase-in-cupertino-2/ |title=Apple makes big land purchase in Cupertino |work=The San Jose Mercury News |first=Brandon |last=Bailey |date=2016-08-13 |access-date=2016-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228201418/http://www.mercurynews.com/2010/11/24/apple-makes-big-land-purchase-in-cupertino-2/ |archive-date=2016-12-28 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2010/11/24/apple-makes-big-land-purchase-in-cupertino-2/ |title=Apple makes big land purchase in Cupertino |work=The San Jose Mercury News |first=Brandon |last=Bailey |date=2016-08-13 |accessdate=2017-05-31 |archive-date=2016-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228201418/http://www.mercurynews.com/2010/11/24/apple-makes-big-land-purchase-in-cupertino-2/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，這個地方曾經是惠普的庫比蒂諾園區，其後來遷到[[帕羅奧圖|帕羅奧圖]]。

2011年6月7日，作為蘋果公司時任行政總裁的喬布斯，向庫帕提諾市議會展示新建築及其周圍的建築設計細節<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gtuz5OmOh_M|title=Steve Jobs Presents to the Cupertino City Council (6/7/11)|id=[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChTGNMh9Ti6cCi6gMCxhBTg City of Cupertino]|medium=YouTube|date=2011-06-07|access-date=2019-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150604140310/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gtuz5OmOh_M|archive-date=2015-06-04|url-status=live}}</ref>。該建築的最初構想由喬布斯提出，並交由[[諾曼·福斯特|諾曼·福斯特]]設計。喬布斯帶領福斯特前往[[愛莫利維爾|愛莫利維爾]]的[[皮克斯|皮克斯]]園區參觀由他親自設計的酷似大教堂的建築，建築在設計之時就將所有的設施都置於一個屋檐之下，他在公司新園區的建設上投入了大量的心血。然而，喬布斯在生前並沒有看到施工開始，他於幾個月後的2011年10月5日去世<ref>{{Cite news|last=Markoff|first=John|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/06/business/steve-jobs-of-apple-dies-at-56.html|title=Apple's Visionary Redefined Digital Age|date=2011-10-05|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-02-16|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>。

2013年10月15日，庫帕提諾市議會經過6個小時的辯論，一致通過了蘋果公司新園區的計劃<ref>{{cite news|last=May|first=Patrick|title=Cupertino council clears huge Apple 'spaceship' campus for liftoff|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/business/ci_24319747/cupertino-council-clears-huge-apple-spaceship-campus-liftoff|accessdate=2013-10-16|newspaper=[[San_Jose_Mercury_News|San Jose Mercury News]]|date=2013-10-15|archive-date=2013-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016134602/http://www.mercurynews.com/business/ci_24319747/cupertino-council-clears-huge-apple-spaceship-campus-liftoff|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此後不久，地面上原建築的拆遷工作開始<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.macrumors.com/2013/12/05/demolition-at-new-apple-campus-2-well-underway/|title = Demolition at New Apple Campus 2 Well Underway|last = Clover|first = Juli|date = 2013-12-05|publisher = [[MacRumors|MacRumors]]|accessdate = 2017-05-31|archive-date = 2016-07-01|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160701123559/http://www.macrumors.com/2013/12/05/demolition-at-new-apple-campus-2-well-underway/|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=May|first=Patrick|title=Cupertino council clears huge Apple 'spaceship' campus for liftoff|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/business/ci_24319747/cupertino-council-clears-huge-apple-spaceship-campus-liftoff|access-date=2013-10-16|newspaper=[[San_Jose_Mercury_News|San Jose Mercury News]]|date=2013-10-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016134602/http://www.mercurynews.com/business/ci_24319747/cupertino-council-clears-huge-apple-spaceship-campus-liftoff|archive-date=2013-10-16|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.macrumors.com/2013/12/05/demolition-at-new-apple-campus-2-well-underway/|title = Demolition at New Apple Campus 2 Well Underway|last = Clover|first = Juli|date = 2013-12-05|publisher = [[MacRumors|MacRumors]]|access-date = 2016-06-22|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160701123559/http://www.macrumors.com/2013/12/05/demolition-at-new-apple-campus-2-well-underway/|archive-date = 2016-07-01|url-status = live}}</ref>。原先計劃在2013年破土動工，並於2015年投入使用，但由於延期的關係，在2014年才得以動工<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/apple/11628710/When-Stephen-Fry-met-Jony-Ive-the-self-confessed-fanboi-meets-Apples-newly-promoted-chief-design-officer.html|title=When Stephen Fry met Jony Ive the self-confessed tech geek talks to Apple's newly promoted chief design officer|publisher=[[The_Telegraph_(U.K.)|The Telegraph]]|work=[[telegraph.co.uk|telegraph.co.uk]]|date=2015-05-26|author=Fry, Stephen|accessdate=2015-05-31|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150531075735/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/apple/11628710/When-Stephen-Fry-met-Jony-Ive-the-self-confessed-fanboi-meets-Apples-newly-promoted-chief-design-officer.html?utm_source=pocket&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=pockethits|archivedate=2015-05-31|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/jobs-s-spaceship-like-apple-offices-to-arrive-later-than-planned.html|title=Jobs’s Spaceship-Like Apple Offices Completion Meets Delays|publisher=Bloomberg|work=Bloomberg.com|date=2012-11-21|author=Peter Burrows|accessdate=2013-02-27|archive-date=2021-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311000021/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/jobs-s-spaceship-like-apple-offices-to-arrive-later-than-planned.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/apple/11628710/When-Stephen-Fry-met-Jony-Ive-the-self-confessed-fanboi-meets-Apples-newly-promoted-chief-design-officer.html|title=When Stephen Fry met Jony Ive the self-confessed tech geek talks to Apple's newly promoted chief design officer|publisher=[[The_Telegraph_(U.K.)|The Telegraph]]|work=[[telegraph.co.uk|telegraph.co.uk]]|date=2015-05-26|author=Fry, Stephen|access-date=2015-05-31| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150531075735/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/apple/11628710/When-Stephen-Fry-met-Jony-Ive-the-self-confessed-fanboi-meets-Apples-newly-promoted-chief-design-officer.html| archive-date= 2015-05-31 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/jobs-s-spaceship-like-apple-offices-to-arrive-later-than-planned.html|title=Jobs's Spaceship-Like Apple Offices Completion Meets Delays|publisher=Bloomberg|work=Bloomberg.com|date=2012-11-21|author=Peter Burrows|access-date=2013-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130308093459/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/jobs-s-spaceship-like-apple-offices-to-arrive-later-than-planned.html|archive-date=2013-03-08|url-status=live}}</ref>。

2017年2月22日，蘋果公司宣布其園區正式命名為「'''蘋果園區'''（Apple Park）」，而未來用於舉行發佈會等活動的禮堂被命名為「'''史蒂夫·喬布斯劇院'''（Steve Jobs Theater）」<ref name="openingdate" />。儘管園區施工仍在繼續，園區還是於2017年4月對工人開放<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/2/22/14696808/apple-park-campus-steve-jobs-theater-april-2017|title=Apple's spaceship campus, Apple Park, opens in April|work=The Verge|access-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626192502/https://www.theverge.com/2017/2/22/14696808/apple-park-campus-steve-jobs-theater-april-2017|archive-date=2018-06-26|url-status=live}}</ref>。史蒂夫·喬布斯劇院的第一場活動隨後於2017年9月12日舉行<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/8/31/16233998/apple-iphone-8-event-september-12th-invitation|title=Apple's iPhone 8 event is happening on September 12th|work=The Verge|access-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831183143/https://www.theverge.com/2017/8/31/16233998/apple-iphone-8-event-september-12th-invitation|archive-date=2017-08-31|url-status=live}}</ref>。'''蘋果園區訪客中心'''（Apple Park Visitor Center）於五天後，即在2017年9月17日開幕<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/apple-park-visitor-center-ar-augmented-reality-open-to-public/|title=You too can now visit the new Apple Park campus|date=2017-11-17|work=CNET|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626000449/https://www.cnet.com/news/apple-park-visitor-center-ar-augmented-reality-open-to-public/|archive-date=2018-06-26|url-status=live}}</ref>。

由於蘋果園區在該地區的存在，周邊的街道迎來了旅遊業的增長，该建筑和公园也是加州和旧金山的主要城市景点之一，隨著當地住屋的房地產價格不斷上漲，經常吸引希望住在鄰近工作場所的蘋果公司員工<ref name="APark side issue NYT 1">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/04/realestate/commercial/apples-park-silicon-valley-cupertino-sunnyvale.html|title=Apple Disrupts Silicon Valley With Another Eye-Catcher: Its New Home|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|first=Kathy Chin|last=Leong|date=2017-07-04|access-date=2017-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719110934/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/04/realestate/commercial/apples-park-silicon-valley-cupertino-sunnyvale.html|archive-date=2017-07-19|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="APark side issue MR 1">{{cite web|url=https://www.macrumors.com/2017/07/05/houses-near-apple-park-tourism|title=Houses Near Apple Park Met With Increased Tourism and Rising Real Estate Values|publisher=[[MacRumors|MacRumors]]|first=Mitchel|last=Broussard|date=2017-07-05|access-date=2017-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829000217/https://www.macrumors.com/2017/07/05/houses-near-apple-park-tourism/|archive-date=2018-08-29|url-status=live}}</ref>。

== 地點 ==
蘋果園區位於原本的[[苹果公司总部|蘋果公司總部]]以東約1.2英里處。蘋果公司自1977年以來一直在庫比蒂諾開展業務，這就是該公司決定於該處建廠而不是搬到更便宜和更遠地方的原因。根據具有地下水羽流的{{le|超級基金修正及再認可法案|Superfund}}，蘋果園區的毗鄰位置有一個受污染的場地<ref>Hugh Biggar (June 7, 2006). ''The Cupertino Courier''.</ref>。

== 設計和施工 ==
[[史蒂夫·乔布斯|史提夫·喬布斯]]在2011年10月去世前的最後一次公開露面中被引述說：
{{cquote|它的中間有一個華麗的庭院，還有更多。這是一個圓形，所以它一直彎曲。這不是以最便宜的方式來構建一些東西。主樓的每一塊玻璃都是彎曲的。我們有機會建造世界上最好的辦公大樓。我真的認為建築系學生要來這裡看看<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2017/02/23/data-sheet-apple-park-steve-jobs|title=Steve Jobs' Legacy Lives On in Apple's New Campus|first=Adam|last=Lashinsky|date=2017-02-23|work=Fortune|access-date=2017-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225214221/http://fortune.com/2017/02/23/data-sheet-apple-park-steve-jobs/|archive-date=2017-02-25|url-status=live}}</ref>。}}
[[File:Apple_Campus_2_aerial_Aug_2016.jpg|thumb]]也顯示於右上角。]]

這標榜為「完美的圓」的環形建築，最初並不是這樣計劃的。每層樓的內圈和外圈都用作步道並保持開放。園區有八座建築物，由九座迷你[[中庭|中庭]]分隔。園區以[[圓周|圓周]]1.6公里，其直徑為{{convert|1512|ft|m}}，其圓形建築容納了大多數員工<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/apple-park-spaceship-campus-headquarters-explained-2017-9|title=Apple is about to reveal its $5 billion campus to the public — here's what you need to know|last=Leswing|first=Kif|website=Business Insider|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。其樓高四層，地下有三層<ref name="wired.com">{{Cite news|last=Levy|first=Steven|url=https://www.wired.com/2017/05/apple-park-new-silicon-valley-campus/|title=Apple's New Campus: An Exclusive Look Inside the Mothership|date=2017-05-16|work=Wired|access-date=2020-02-16|language=en-US|issn=1059-1028}}</ref>。蘋果的公司為建築物的所有部分創建了真人大小的模型以分析任何設計問題。

該設計將道路和停車場隱藏在地下。園區只有使用玻璃作為牆壁和看到內園的景色，以及面向建築物外部的景觀<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/16/17020246/apple-park-headquarters-employees-injury-glass-doors-design|title=Apple employees can't stop walking into the beautiful glass doors at new Apple Park campus|last=Garun|first=Natt|date=2018-02-16|website=The Verge|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://architizer.com/blog/inspiration/stories/architectural-details-apple-park-windows/|title=How the World's Largest Curved Windows Were Forged for Apple HQ - Architizer Journal|date=2017-08-09|website=Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。建築中有大約{{convert|83,000|sqft|m2}}的空間用於會議和分組討論。圓形建築的內部包含一個{{convert|30|acre|ha|adj=on}}的公園，公園內有一個池塘、加州果樹和蜿蜒小徑，靈感來自加州果園。喬布斯希望沒有可見的接縫、間隙或畫筆筆觸，以實踐潔淨的合身和表面處理。

所有用於室內傢俱的木材均來自特定種類的[[楓屬|楓木]]，蘋果公司與來自19個國家／地區的建築公司就設計和材料展開合作<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macworld.co.uk/feature/apple/complete-guide-apple-park-3489704/|title=Video shows drone crashing on to Apple Park's roof|last=Moore|first=Amy|website=Macworld UK|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。大樓以透氣的空心混凝土板充當地板、天花板和[[暖通空調|暖通空調]]系統。園區總共使用了4,300塊這樣的木板<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://appleinsider.com/articles/16/06/11/new-apple-campus-2-tour-highlights-breathing-concrete-glass-panels-power-tech-more|title=New Apple Campus 2 tour highlights 'breathing' concrete, glass panels, power tech & more|last1=Saturday|first1=Roger Fingas|last2=June 11|website=AppleInsider|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16|last3=2016|last4=PT|first4=04:41 pm}}</ref>。一些板塊重量為{{convert|60,000|lb|t}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/apple-campus-2-construction-tour-cupertino-2016-6|title=Apple gave a private tour of its new 'spaceship' campus — here's what it was like|last=Science|first=Xavier Harding, Popular|website=Business Insider|language=en|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>。

=== 建造 ===
在施工過程中，這座建築的結構是由DPR／[[斯堪卡|斯堪卡]]設計的，但由於未公開的原因，他們被免職<ref>{{cite news |last1=Donato-Weinstein |first1=Nathan |title=Apple to completely part ways with DPR/Skanska on Apple Campus 2 within weeks |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/news/2015/06/09/apple-to-completely-part-ways-with-dpr-skanska-on.html |access-date=2018-12-09 |work=Silicon Valley Business Journal |publisher=American City Business Journals |date=2015-06-09 |location=San Jose |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617022240/http://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/news/2015/06/09/apple-to-completely-part-ways-with-dpr-skanska-on.html |archive-date=2017-06-17 |url-status=live }}</ref>。{{le|魯道夫和斯萊頓|Rudolph and Sletten}}和底座施工（Holder Construction）竣工了結構、單位與內部擴建<ref name="Donato1">{{cite news |last1=Donato-Weinstein |first1=Nathan |title=Apple hires new spaceship general contractor as questions swirl about construction delays |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/news/2015/05/04/apple-hires-news-spaceship-generalcontractor-as.html |access-date=2018-12-09 |work=Silicon Valley Business Journal |publisher=American City Business Journals |date=2015-05-04 |location=San Jose |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702160956/http://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/news/2015/05/04/apple-hires-news-spaceship-generalcontractor-as.html |archive-date=2017-07-02 |url-status=live }}</ref>。當時稱為BNBTBuilders的特魯貝克建築（Truebeck Construction）負責外部景觀、史蒂夫喬布斯劇院和健康及健身中心；麥卡錫建築公司（McCarthy Building Companies）建造了停車場；以及，花崗岩建築（Granite Construction）進行了道路拓寬和公用事業工程<ref name="Donato1" />。門面窗格由巴伐利亞公司{{le|西爾有限公司|seele GmbH}}生產<ref>{{Cite news|date=2016-02-22|title=Apple-Hauptquartier: Fenster stellt Firma aus Bayern her|work=[[Die_Welt|Die Welt]]|url=https://www.welt.de/wirtschaft/article152524308/Ein-Teil-des-Apple-Raumschiffs-kommt-aus-Bayern.html|access-date=2020-09-24}}</ref>。

